{{Infobox football biography | name= Bessam | fullname = Cheikh El Khalil Moulaye Ahmed | image = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1987|12|4|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Zouérat]], [[Mauritania]] | height = {{convert|1.80|m|ftin|0|abbr=on}} | currentclub = [[FC Nouadhibou]] | clubnumber = 10 | position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]] | youthyears1= | youthclubs1= | years1 = 2013–2014 | clubs1 = [[ACS Ksar]] | caps1 = - | goals1 = - | years2 = 2014–2015 | clubs2 = [[JS Kabylie]] | caps2 = 14 | goals2 = 2 | years3 = 2015–2016 | clubs3 = [[CS Constantine]] | caps3 = 29 | goals3 = 3 | years4 = 2016–2017 | clubs4 = [[Al-Ansar SC|Al-Ansar]] | caps4 = 1 | goals4 = | years5 = 2017–2018 | clubs5 = [[Al-Ahly Tripoli]] | caps5 = | goals5 = | years6 = 2018– | clubs6 = [[FC Nouadhibou]] | caps6 = | goals6 = | nationalyears1= 2013– | nationalteam1= [[Mauritania national football team|Mauritania]]<ref name="NFT">{{NFT player|pid=4297}}</ref> | nationalcaps1= 31 | nationalgoals1 = 12 | ntupdate = 24 March 2017 }}
'''Cheikh El Khalil Moulaye Ahmed''', more commonly known as '''Bessam''', ({{lang-ar|شيخ مولاي أحمد}}; born 4 December 1987 in [[Zouérat]]) is a [[Mauritania]]n football player who currently plays for [[Ligue 1 Mauritania]] club [[FC Nouadhibou]] and the [[Mauritania national football team|Mauritania national team]].
== ACS Ksar == Bessam started his career with the club [[ASC Ksar]] until he was called to represent the national team by the "then" coach [[Patrice Neveu]]. He scored on his first game with the national team, and made an assist in the 2-0 win over Senegal that Qualified the Mauritanian team to the [[2014 African Nations Championship]] in [[South Africa]].
==JS Kabylie== In May 2014, Bessam signed a two-year contract with [[Algeria]]n club [[JS Kabylie]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mauritaniefootball.com/bessam-un-mauritanien-au-jsk-pour-2-ans/ |title=Officiel : Bessam , un mauritanien au JSK en Algérie pour 2 ans |publisher=Mauritanie Football |language=French |accessdate=2014-08-07}}</ref> On August 16, he made his JS Kabylie debut, away to [[MC Oran]], scoring the second goal in a 2–0 victory.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lebuteur.com/article/detail?titre=mco-0-jsk-2-entame-de-saison-reussie-pour-les-kabyles&id=12408|title=MCO 0 - JSK 2 : Entame de saison réussie pour les Kabyles !|author=Amine L.|publisher=Le Buteur|language=French|date=August 16, 2014|accessdate=August 18, 2014}}</ref> He scored the first goal for Mauritania in a 2-0 victory over Senegal.
