[[File:The club house - geograph.org.uk - 292769.jpg|thumb|Langland Bay Golf Clubhouse]] [[File:Towards Rams Tor - geograph.org.uk - 150720.jpg|thumb|A view from the course]] '''Langland Bay Golf Club''' is an 18-hole golf course known in an [[Area of Outstanding Natural Beauty]] overlooking [[Langland Bay]] near [[Swansea]], [[Wales]], UK.<ref name=Ozfinance>{{cite news|first=Craig |last=Tansley |url=http://www.afr.com/lifestyle/travel/the-green-green-grass-of-tom-jones-home-20160307-gnccez |title=The green, green grass of Tom Jones' home |date=24 March 2016 |work=The Australian Financial Review |accessdate=2016-03-25}}</ref>
The first evidence of a golf club at Langland Bay is a minute book dating from 1901. The golf course was officially opened on 10 September 1904.<ref name=history>{{cite web |url=http://www.langlandbaygolfclub.com/the-club/club-history/ |title=Club History |publisher=Langland Bay Golf Club |accessdate=2016-03-25}}</ref> The centenary in 2004 was marked by special events and a visit from [[Prince Andrew, Duke of York]].<ref name=history />
The club's members claim Hole 6 is the most difficult in Wales,<ref name=challengeanddelight>{{cite news |url=http://www.southwales-eveningpost.co.uk/18-golf-holes-South-West-Wales-challenge-delight/story-28785105-detail/story.html |title=18 golf holes in South West Wales that will challenge and delight the most demanding of players |date=22 February 2016 |work=South Wales Evening Post |accessdate=2016-03-25}}</ref> while Hole 16 is known as "Death Or Glory" with the sea on one side and a 100 feet steep drop on the other.<ref name=carradice53>{{Citation |author=Trudy Carradice |url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=szqIAwAAQBAJ&pg=PT53#v=onepage&q&f=false |title=Golf in Wales: A Pictorial History |publisher=Amberley Publishing |year=2013 |page=53 |isbn=978-1-445623474}}</ref> The other holes typically have small greens and plenty of rough grass and sand traps.<ref name=carradice53 /> The sea can be easily seen from 15 of its 18 holes.<ref name=Ozfinance />
The club hosts the Gwalia PGA Pro-Am tournament each year, raising money for the Gwalia Housing Trust.<ref name=priceheadlineact>{{cite news|first=Anthony |last=Woolford |url=http://www.walesonline.co.uk/sport/other-sport/golf/ryder-cup-star-phillip-price-9463748 |title=Ryder Cup star Phillip Price is the headline act at the Gwalia Trust Langland Bay Pro-Am |date=16 June 2015 |work=Wales Online |accessdate=2016-03-25}}</ref>
