{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2013}} {{Infobox stadium | name = Sakarya Sports Hall | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image =Sakarya Spor Salonu.jpg | caption = | fullname = Sakarya Spor Salonu | former_names = | location = Yazlık Mah. [[Serdivan]], [[Adapazarı]], Turkey | coordinates = {{coord|40|47|13|N|30|22|06|E|display=inline,title}} | broke_ground = May 25, 2011 | built = | opened = {{Start date and age|2013|06|24}} | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = Youth and Sports Directorate of Sakarya Province | operator = | surface = | scoreboard = | cost = {{Turkish lira}} 30 million (approx. US$ 18.75 million <small>in May 2011</small>) | architect = | project_manager = | capacity = 5,000 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | acreage = {{convert|21000|m2|acre|abbr=on}} | tenants = [[Sakarya BB]] (2017–present) | embedded = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> }} '''Sakarya Sports Hall''' ({{lang-tr|Sakarya Spor Salonu}}) is a multi-purpose [[indoor arena]] located at Yazlık neighborhood of [[Serdivan]] district in [[Adapazarı]], [[Sakarya Province]], Turkey.
The venue is used for competitions and trainings of a wide variety of sports branches including basketball, volleyball, handball, fencing, table tennis, wrestling, judo, karate, kick boxing and taekwondo. The sports hall was built in a land covering {{convert|21000|m2|acre|abbr=on}}, which was granted to the Youth and Sports Directorate of Sakarya Province by the Serdivan municipality on September 1, 2010.<ref name="ih1"/> The construction, which was projected to cost {{Turkish lira}} 30 million (approx. US$ 18.75 million in May 2011), began with a ground breaking ceremony held on May 25, 2011.<ref name="sv"/> Opened officially on June 24, 2013, the facility has a seating capacity of 5,000.<ref name="sy1"/>
