{{Infobox athletics race | bgcolour = #27b096 | image = Taipei International Marathon 2012 Route map.png | caption = Taipei Marathon route map | date = December | location = [[Taipei]], [[Taiwan]] | type = [[Road running|road]] | distance = [[Marathon]] | sponsor = | beneficiary = | est = 1986 | record = | homepage = {{URL|https://www.sportsnet.org.tw/|Taipei Marathon}} | participants = }} The '''Fubon Taipei International Marathon''' is a series of road races sponsored by [[Fubon]] (formerly sponsored by ING from 2004-08 until Fubon acquired ING's Taiwan division) in [[Taipei]], [[Taiwan]]. This marathon competition made great impacts on recruiting local volunteers from financial, academical, and governmental people, importing "[[ChampionChip]]" timer system for elite marathon runners, and setting up "Kids Running Group" and "Police & Firefighters Group" from 2005.
[[File:2006INGTaipeiMarathon-046.jpg|thumb|Starting of 2006 ING Taipei International Marathon]]
Due to the bad traffic issues in Taiwan, many academic, foreigners, and media criticized this issue at 2004.{{Citation needed|date=December 2008}} ING Antai even attempted to quit the sponsoring, but finally canceled this idea with a coordination between [[Chinese Taipei Road Running Association]] and [[Taipei City Government]], who promised for good traffic quality to participants on 15 December 2006, and the marathon has been sponsored by ING, and later Fubon, since then. After the success in 2006, this competition was finally nominated to "Taiwan Sports Elite Awards".{{Citation needed|date=December 2008}}
