{{Infobox sportsperson | name = | image = | caption = | fullname = Taretiita Baraniko Tabaroua | nickname = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1994|11|29|df=y}} | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | nationality = | residence = | years_active = | height = | weight = {{convert|75.94|kg|lb|abbr=on}} | website = | country = {{flagu|Kiribati}} | sport = [[Olympic weightlifting|Weightlifting]] | weight_class = 77 kg | pb = | club = | team = National team | coach = | retired = | show-medals = | medaltemplates = | medaltemplates-title = | updated = 19 October 2016 }} '''Taretiita Baraniko Tabaroua''' (born {{birth date|1994|11|29|df=y}}) is a I-Kiribati male [[Olympic weightlifting|weightlifter]], competing in the 77 kg category and representing Kiribati at international competitions. He won the silver medal at the [[2016 Oceania Weightlifting Championships]], lifting a total of 290 kg. He participated at the [[2014 Commonwealth Games]] in the [[Weightlifting at the 2014 Commonwealth Games – Men's 77 kg|77 kg event]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Weightlifting at the 2014 Commonwealth Games - Taretiita Baraniko Tabaroua|url=http://www.iwf.net/results/results-by-events/?event=291|publisher=iwf.net|accessdate=23 June 2016}}</ref>
